description:
A well established organization in the banking domain is seeking a dynamic operational risk manager (UORM) for their Product Control division.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in finance or accounting ;
• At least 5 years of experience in operational risk management and governance in the financial services sector;
• Proficient in risk controls and processes associated with product control function;
• Basic understanding of accounting and treasury transaction life cycle;
• Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
• Out of the box thinker with good attention to details.

Desirable Skill(s)
• Prior experience in banking;
• CFA certification;
• Ability to leverage analytics to gain insights.

Responsibilities
• Responsible for the risk management and governance related to the Product Control processes;
• Assess existing risk monitoring tools and processes for effectiveness and drive related enhancements;
• Validate risk events for factual accuracy, identify cause and remedial... measures/action plans to prevent recurrence;
• Continuously monitor risks and identify weaknesses in risk controls and processes;
• Conduct risk related processes like Risk & Control Self-Assessment (RCSA), Business Continuity Planning (BCM) and Quality Assurance Review;
• Act as a central liaison party to collaborate with internal and external personnel for audits, regulatory inspections;
• Track and monitor the execution of action plans and audit based recommendations;
• Keep abreast of vulnerabilities in product control processes and continuously enhance the risk governance framework

